<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><?ish ishref="GUID-90D318BD-4695-46A9-B882-323F531C80F4" version="1" lang="en-US"?><task xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="GUID-90D318BD-4695-46A9-B882-323F531C80F4" xml:lang="en-US" ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.3" domains="(topic task)                            (topic hi-d)                            (topic ui-d)                            (topic sw-d)                            (topic indexing-d)                            (topic ut-d)                            a(base ishcondition)                            a(base varid)                            a(base varref)                            a(base cid)                            a(base partslist)                            (topic oce-d)                            (topic sdlVariables-c)                            (topic oceCommonElements-c)                            (topic oceMetaDecl-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c task oceTask-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c hi-d oceHighlight-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c ui-d oceUi-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c sw-d oceSoftware-c)   " class="- topic/topic task/task "><title class="- topic/title ">11 Download and prepare the software package for upgrade with Settings Editor</title><abstract class="- topic/abstract " id="M140828-B205"><p class="- topic/p ">The system software of the Colorado 1635 (for upgrade with Settings Editor) consists of 6 .exe files : 
</p><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> 3 exe files containing the operating system (...OS...) 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> 3 exe files containing the PRISMAsync application software (...PS...) 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">1 exe file containing the GPL part of the software (open source software). 
</p></li></ul><p class="- topic/p "> This procedure describes how get these files and how to prepare them for use. 
</p></abstract><prolog class="- topic/prolog "><metadata class="- topic/metadata "><category class="- topic/category ">Installation</category></metadata></prolog><taskbody class="- topic/body task/taskbody "><section id="GUID-25DF7D5E-8B40-43FF-92AD-EC0D01CB01A4" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Required tools</title><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">A download site where you can get the software. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> This is site is listed in the release bulletin for this software release. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">An MD5 checksum tool to verify the zip file after the download. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Tools like: http: 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">- www.md5summer.org, 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">- windows internal scripting ( win10 via command prompt: CertUtil -hashfile &lt;path to file&gt; MD5 ) 
</p></li></ul></section><section id="SECTION_8B2EDF5F2405440097F73F1429FA79F0" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Procedure</title><table id="GUID-44E51CAE-2EF5-431B-BFBB-AE0F0810C645" class="- topic/table "><tgroup cols="2" align="left" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="10*" align="left" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="90*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead class="- topic/thead "><row valign="top" class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Step 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody class="- topic/tbody "><row valign="top" class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" align="left" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">1 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" align="left" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Go to the dowload site and login as described in the bulletin. 
</p></entry></row><row valign="top" class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" align="left" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">2 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" align="left" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Go to the For_SE directory. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> You will find a .zip file and an .md5 file. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> In this case 2.1.1.0 is shown: 
</p><fig id="GUID-535535C6-505D-41EE-91C6-ADD6DB2CCACF" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-A728D821-134B-4685-91F3-7B1A5BF10C7C-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-A728D821-134B-4685-91F3-7B1A5BF10C7C-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row valign="top" class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" align="left" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">3 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" align="left" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Download the .zip file and the .md5 to a convenient location. You need approximately 10 Gb of storage area. 
</p></entry></row><row valign="top" class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" align="left" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">4 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" align="left" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Check the md5 of the zip. File verification via MD5 is a generic mechanism. A lot of verification tools exist. Use one of the tools from the required tools section in case you have no tooling installed or doubt the outcome of your own tool. 
</p></entry></row><row valign="top" class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" align="left" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">5 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" align="left" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Unzip the downloaded zip file. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> Where in this case R2.1.2.0 is shown. 
</p><fig id="GUID-CC99A96E-FD2E-4723-BD03-37AE2B0CDAF2" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-E97AAA8E-C25F-40BC-AB96-84D50ADD8BEC-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-E97AAA8E-C25F-40BC-AB96-84D50ADD8BEC-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row valign="top" class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" align="left" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">6 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" align="left" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> The .exe files can now be used to perform a software upgrade with Settings Editor. 
</p></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section></taskbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-724C7F1C-09E3-4D8F-B77B-2B159E768314.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>Installation</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
